FishEye shows git related Activity Stream data ordered by AuthorDate as result of {{git log}} command. It will be awesome if it shows data ordered by CommitDate. In order to do this, this command could be used:

{noformat}git log --pretty=fuller{noformat}

To satisfy all customers maybe we can create a checkbox or dropdown that would show both options (CommitDate and AuthorDate).

For the following API:
{code}
http://localhost:8060/rest-service-fe/changeset-v1/listChangesets/
{code}
In our [Doc|http://docs.atlassian.com/fisheye-crucible/latest/wadl/fisheye.html#d2e131], we don't explain how the "expand" parameter should be defined. If this parameter is not defined, the API always return "empty" results.

JIRA uses:
{code}
http://localhost:8060/rest-service-fe/changeset-v1/listChangesets/?expand=changesets[-21:-1].revisions[0:29]&comment=XXXX-1&p4JobFixed=XXXX-1&rep=My_Repo
{code}

