Attempting to create a review in Crucible from the command-line fails if the XML document contains a copyright symbol.

Attached find two XML documents, one with and one without the copyright symbol.  Create a project in Crucible and edit the XML files appropriately.  Find below the *curl* command I used to post the reviews (Windows).

{code}
curl -u mike:jira -H "Content-Type: application/xml" http://localhost:8060/rest-service/reviews-v1 -d @cru_copyright.xml
{code}

and

{code}
curl -u mike:jira -H "Content-Type: application/xml" http://localhost:8060/rest-service/reviews-v1 -d @cru_no_copyright.xml
{code}

Note that the if the copyright symbol is replaced with either of the following the review is created successfully and Crucible displays the copyright symbol properly:

{code}
&#169;
{code}

{code}
&#xA9;
{code}




{code}
curl -u mike:jira -H "Content-Type: application/xml" http://localhost:8060/rest-service/reviews-v1 -d @cru_no_copyright.xml
{code}

When an [outbound proxy|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/FISHEYE/How+Do+I+Confugure+an+Outbound+Proxy+Server+for+FishEye] is configured, this is ignored by the hg calls.

E.g. FishEye calls
{noformat}
"hg --config ui.verbose=false pull https://bitbucket.org/atlassian_dragons/dragonslayers "
{noformat}
instead of
{noformat}
"hg --config ui.verbose=false --config http_proxy.host=PROXY_IP:PORT pull https://bitbucket.org/atlassian_dragons/dragonslayers "
{noformat}

A workaround is to configure the proxy settings in {{.hgrc}}.
